<item>
            <title>[LU-1202] Error during downgrade test</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1202</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During downgrade test, I met this problem,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@client-15 tests&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# ls /mnt/lustre/&lt;br/&gt;
ls: cannot access /mnt/lustre/d0.upgrade-downgrade: No such file or directory&lt;br/&gt;
d0.upgrade-downgrade&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;what I did is following&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   1. setup and start Lustre 1.8.x filesystem&lt;br/&gt;
   2. extract a kernel tarball into a Lustre test directory&lt;br/&gt;
   3. shutdown the entire Lustre filesystem&lt;br/&gt;
   4. upgrade all Lustre servers and clients at once to Lustre 2.x&lt;br/&gt;
   5. start the entire Lustre filesystem&lt;br/&gt;
   6. extract the same kernel tarball into a new Lustre test directory&lt;br/&gt;
   7. compare the old and new test directories (no difference)&lt;br/&gt;
   8. run auster test suite&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Clean downgrade &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   9. setup and start Lustre 2.x filesystem (upgraded from Lustre 1.8.x)&lt;br/&gt;
   10. extract a kernel tarball into a Lustre test directory&lt;br/&gt;
   11. shutdown the entire Lustre filesystem&lt;br/&gt;
   12. downgrade all Lustre servers and clients at once to Lustre 1.8.x&lt;br/&gt;
   13. start the entire Lustre filesystem&lt;br/&gt;
   14. extract the same kernel tarball into a new Lustre test directory&lt;br/&gt;
   15. compare the old and new test directories (no difference)&lt;br/&gt;
---found this problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The attachment is the console message from the MDS node.  &lt;/p&gt;

</description>
